.TH "adjust_jiffies" 9 "adjust_jiffies" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
adjust_jiffies \- Adjust the system "loops_per_jiffy".
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" adjust_jiffies
.BI "(unsigned long val "  ","
.BI "struct cpufreq_freqs *ci "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "val" 12
CPUFREQ_PRECHANGE or CPUFREQ_POSTCHANGE.
.IP "ci" 12
Frequency change information.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function alters the system "loops_per_jiffy" for the clock
speed change. Note that loops_per_jiffy cannot be updated on SMP
systems as each CPU might be scaled differently. So, use the arch
per-CPU loops_per_jiffy value wherever possible.
